The other records ol the eyre of 1221 are almost or quite as bulky as this Gloucestershire roll, and if these be compared with the brief iter rolls ol Richard’s reign, printed by Palgrave, the conclusion that in 1221 there had been no eyre lor along time past will seem the more prohable.

We must not, however, suppose that Gloucestershire had been quite without penal justice. There may have been gaol deliveries.

We shall hear ol one (date unknown) by Henry de Vere ⁸. But¹
